&gt;&gt;&gt; For large aeas like Gettysburg, ffort Mifflin, ESP, etc, what we do
&gt;&gt; is map out the area ahead of time, with a scheduled rotation of small
&gt;&gt; groups. That way we know where everyone is at all times. So far this
&gt;&gt; has been successful for us. This method assumes a level of
&gt;&gt; responsibility and respect on the part of the investigators - I have
&gt;&gt; found that if you are doing an event where others and the public are
&gt;&gt; invited it is essential to have them see the schedule and agree to
&gt;&gt; abide by it when they sign up and then again when they arrive.
